25/10/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Serbian Radical Party (SRS) leader Vojislav Seselj, who is on trial at The Hague war crimes tribunal, plans to undergo minor heart surgery, legal adviser Zoran Krasic announced on Sunday (October 24th). No date has been set yet. Seselj faces charges for war crimes committed against non-Serbs in Croatia, Vojvodina and Bosnia and Herzegovina between 1991 and 1993. His trial began in November 2007. (Tanjug, Vecernje Novosti - 24/10/10)
